node.title: Skipper missing, four others rescued after boat capsizes in WA's north
node.alt: Kevin Haley and Sonia Gardner in a hallway.
node.description: A man in his 50s is missing but four of his passengers including two girls are found safe and well walking through marshland after their boat overturns near Derby in WA.
node.content: ["A man in his 50s is missing but four of his passengers have been found safe and well after their boat capsized near Derby in Western Australia's far north.", "Police were notified that the boat, carrying two men, a woman and two girls, had overturned at Airport Creek, 5 kilometres south-west of Derby, about 1:45pm yesterday.", "Police said the 6.4-metre vessel had left Derby Jetty about 12:30pm.", "An air and marine search was launched, including a helicopter and an Australian Maritime Safety Authority jet.", "About 5:40pm\u00a0last night, the helicopter spotted the overturned boat on the shoreline, about 17 kilometres south of where it capsized.", "Police said the helicopter pilot also saw footprints in the mud and officers found four passengers walking through marshland about an hour later.", "The man, a woman and the two children were uninjured but were taken to Derby Hospital for observation.", "The boat's skipper is still unaccounted for and police said an air, marine and land search for him would continue today."]
